    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00baC/ 200\u00baC (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Melt a knob of <strong>butter </strong>in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once soft, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Gradually add 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to the pan until no lumps remain</p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tortiglioni </strong>and<strong> </strong>100ml<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>cold</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a medium heat and cook for 8 min or until the tortiglioni is cooked with a slight bite and the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is cooked, remove from the heat and add the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> dill </strong>and your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong></p><p>Season generously with<strong> pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>chopped smoked basa </strong>through the creamy pasta until well coated \u2013 this is your <strong>fish pie pasta</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>fish pie pasta</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until the basa is cooked through and the pasta is golden on top \u2013 this is your <strong>fish pie pasta bake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add<strong> </strong>to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fish-pie-pasta-bake-with-dressed-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fish pie pasta bake</strong> with the<strong> dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
